commitResults.messageTitle: Add Assignment class and list of Assignments to Student class
commitResults.messageBody:
This commit adds a new Assignment class to the student package, which encapsulates the description and deadline of a particular assignment. The class is implemented with a constructor that takes the required fields as parameters, as well as getters to access the fields.

In addition, this commit modifies the Student class to include a list of Assignment objects. This list is initialized in the constructor with an empty ArrayList, and there are corresponding methods for adding and removing assignments from the list. The toString method of the Student class has also been updated to include the list of assignments.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix the Styling Issue of the last Commit and Simplify Student card
commitResults.messageBody: Since we are displaying the student's profile with a view profile button, it is only reasonable to hide the full information from the student card and display it on the student info page.

Added a new class CreateHomeworkCommandParser that parses user input and creates a new CreateHomeworkCommand object. The parser validates the user input and throws a ParseException if the input does not conform to the expected format. The CreateHomeworkCommand contains a NameContainsKeywordsPredicate, a homework name, and a deadline.

This commit adds a new command view-homework to the system that allows tutors to view homework for specified students with an option to filter by status. The command uses a ViewHomeworkCommand class to handle the logic of filtering homework and a ViewHomeworkCommandParser class to parse user input.

The command takes in optional parameters n/STUDENT_NAME and st/STATUS that allow tutors to filter homework by student name and status respectively. By default, all homework will be displayed. The available status values are completed and pending.

This commit updates the storage function in TutorPro to allow for the storage of assignments for each student. The Student class has been updated to include a List of Homework objects, representing the assignments for that student. The StorageManager class has been updated to support the saving and loading of these Homework objects in the data file. Additionally, the ModelManager class has been updated to provide methods for adding and removing Homework objects from a Student's list of assignments, and for retrieving the list of assignments for a given Student. These changes enable TutorPro to more effectively manage student assignments and progress.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Exam class to encapsulate the exam of a student
commitResults.messageBody: In this commit, an Exam class has been added to the project to encapsulate the exam of a student. The Exam class contains fields for the exam score and the full marks, as well as methods for calculating the percentage score and formatting the exam as a string. The Exam class also includes unit tests to ensure proper functionality.
